<paragraph id="8B98B1107CFE308045FD3D95B9C0A1F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">The genus includes 45 described species and many undescribed species distributed mainly in tropical and subtropical regions; a few species extend into the temperate zone.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD7FE68F76277DD328C204783A6B9995" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
In China five described species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="DA2A54D95F1347484E7D3AF8B1522467" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Araeopteron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Araeopteron" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
